@section('content')
<div class="container">
    <h1>Create New User</h1>

    <form action="{{ route('users.store') }}" method="POST">
        @csrf
        <div class="form-group">
            <label>Name:</label>
            <input type="text" name="name" class="form-control" required>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <label>Email:</label>
            <input type="email" name="email" class="form-control" required>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <label>Password:</label>
            <input type="password" name="password" class="form-control" required>
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
    </form>
</div>
@endsection
```

#### show.blade.php
```html
@extends('layouts.app')

@section('content')
<div class="container">
    <h1>Show User</h1>

    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">User Details</h5>
            <p class="card-text"><strong>ID:</strong> {{ $user->id }}</p>
            <p class="card-text"><strong>Name:</strong> {{ $user->name }}</p>
            <p class="card-text"><strong>Email:</strong> {{ $user->email }}</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <a href="{{ route('users.index') }}" class="btn btn-primary mt-3">Back</a>
</div>
@endsection
```

### 5. Add Routes
Edit `routes/web.php`:
```php
use App\Http\Controllers\UserController;

Route::resource('users', UserController::class);
```

### 6. Create Layout (optional)
Create `resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php` for consistent layout.

### 7. Run Application
```bash
php artisan serve
```

Access CRUD operations at:
- List users: http://localhost:8000/users
- Create user: http://localhost:8000/users/create
- Edit user: http://localhost:8000/users/{id}/edit

### Notes:
1. Password is stored in plain text (use `bcrypt($request->password)` for production)
2. Add authentication middleware if needed
3. Add more validation as needed
4. Consider using Laravel's built-in Auth system for user management

This implementation provides full CRUD functionality with basic validation and pagination. You can customize the views and add more features as needed.

